sentences: Leo van Doeselaar (born 1954, Goes) is a Dutch classical organist and conductor.
He was awarded by the Prix d'Excellence in organ in 1979.
In 1995 he was appointed Professor at the Universität der Künste in Berlin.
Leo van Doeselaar studied the organ (with Albert de Klerk) and piano (with Jan Wijn) at the Amsterdam Sweelinck Conservatory.
